goals.question: What is the distribution of flight delays?
goals.rationale: This tells us how many flights are delayed and by how much time. It can help us identify patterns and trends in flight delays.

goals.question: What is the average flight time for different airlines?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of airline vs. average flight time
goals.rationale: This can help us compare the performance of different airlines in terms of flight duration. It can also help us identify which airlines have longer or shorter flights.

goals.question: What is the relationship between departure delay and arrival delay?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of departure_delay vs. arrival_delay
goals.rationale: This can help us understand if there is a correlation between departure delay and arrival delay. It can also help us identify outliers and anomalies in the data.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight distances?
goals.rationale: This tells us how far the flights are traveling. It can help us identify patterns and trends in flight distances and also help us understand the range of distances covered by the flights.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight cancellations?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of cancellation_code vs. count
goals.rationale: This can help us understand the reasons for flight cancellations and which cancellation codes are most common. It can also help us identify if there are any patterns or trends in flight cancellations.

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='departure_delay', bins=50)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    avg_flight_time = data.groupby('airline')['flight_time'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='airline', y='flight_time', data=avg_flight_time)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average flight time for different airlines?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
